nt color=#FFE081>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://www.elvenelite.com/images/cellpic3.gif class=headings><font color=#FFE081>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#BA9F70><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/belvenelite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=candraverbena>Candra Verbena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Regular</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(5/13/03 3:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=99.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~eden444/images/candra_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possession</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The City of High Elves - Felwithe<br>
<br>
The Pond</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The oracle Willius strolled casually along the cobblestone streets of Felwithe. It was the start of summer and a pleasant heat tinged the exotic night. Hints of festivity teased the barbarian's senses. Colorful, paper lanterns were strung across the facades of gleaming buildings and between them as well. Delicious aromas and the noise of mirth-inspiring music filled the air he breathed. With such sensation all around him, Willius couldn't help but channel the cheer that filled his spirit through the generous smile that split his handsome face. He allowed scent and sound to guide him through the winding streets and deliver him to the source of the merriment.<br>
<br>
Various faces were gathered along the banks of the city's shimmering pond. The light of the moon and hanging lanterns cast a flattering glow thatenhanced smiles and was partially dismissed a few grim looks. Still some distance outside the gathering of merrymakers, Willius took pause to survey the crowd before melting into it.<br>
<br>
He breathed a long sigh as he considered this body of mostly familiar faces that was the Elven Elite. It was the guild that had been his home until only recently. The Northman's memories came to celebrate with him, recalling the great battles, the hard struggles, and deeply satisfying victories of his tenure with the Elite. It was not an unpleasant moment to remember the good times and the bad. Willius was not a being to regret his past as he knew that it was the sum of his experience that made him the shaman he was today.<br>
<br>
&quot;Willius!&quot; a voice from the crowd interrupted Wilius' reverie. His thoughts returned to the present and his senses scanned the crowd briefly before finding the crier who hailed his arrival.<br>
<br>
&quot;Aryllyian!&quot; He greeted the shining, High Elf paladin with an enthusiastic salute before the two clasped hands, both chuckling at his formal greeting. At Aryllyian's side was the high priestess Irislilly, whom Willius greeted with a toothy grin and a respectful bow.<br>
<br>
Willius chuckled as humor re-shaped the Erudite priestess' smile, &quot;We've been friends too long to stand on airs now, Willius.&quot; She told him before seizing him with a hug as warm as the smile spread across her lips.<br>
<br>
&quot;So true, Iris,&quot; he said, heartily accepting her welcome.<br>
<br>
Aryllyian waited for their embrace to break before speaking again, &quot;I'm so glad you could join us tonight as we honor the solstice and each other.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye,&quot; Willius replied, laughing loudly. &quot;Any reason ta celebrate with stiff drinks and good friends is just fine by me!&quot;<br>
<br>
The attention of the two brought on the notice of the many and Willius soon found himself on the receiving end of a line of welcomes, salutes, handshakes and hugs; and the majority of them sincere. The barbarian was no wallflower and responded with the humor that had won him such a list of friends and a few enemies. And though warmed by their greetings, Willius quickly tired of all the social niceties and found himself wishing the lot of them would just return to whatever distractions were being had before his arrival.<br>
<br>
It was quite a bit of time before his wish was granted. In the end he found himself standing against the wall of some quaint building, his fourth pitcher ale in hand, surrounded by a few laughing faces. His company consisted of the High Elf Spindley and his recent bride Lorrelei, and the Wood Elf lovers Giltaav and Kyeneia.  It was the ranger Giltaav who looked after the smiles that lit their faces with the telling of some recent adventure. Willius was only half-listening however. The bulk of his attention moved through the crowd, observing and searching through the various cliques.<br>
<br>
He considered Seyah, Krushh, Eillail, Sparkes and Laenyal as they conversed near the forge, noted their seemingly pleasant expressions and spent no time musing over the content of their discussion. He glanced a small assembly at the water's edge to find Wood Elf Wyture sandwiched between the contesting, hard looks of the Troll Nanbkek and his rival, the Half Elf Muzzic as a few others looked on with grinning expressions. Willius' thoughts lingered on the threesome at the heart of that group and he couldn't help but speculate on what words or regards were moving between them. He grinned as well.<br>
<br>
An explosion of laughter reigned Willius' attention back to his to the motley of friends before him. A light blush filled his cheeks as he realized the small group had swelled and now included the Vah Shir Nalitra, the High Elf cleric Spiritene and their respective companions, both Barbarians, Lucman and Jaered. Willius shook his head and secretly hoped his distraction was not so obvious.<br>
<br>
Where is she hiding? The question swam through his frustrated mind as he breathed what was meant to be a slight sigh, but sounded out as a hard grunt. More than a few pairs of eyes turned to regard him, the expressions surrounding them amused and curious.<br>
<br>
&quot;I need to move around,&quot; Willius grumbled. He peeled away from the wall that supported his back and ignored the giggles of a few knowing souls in the crowd around him.<br>
<br>
Willius walked away from the crowd, away from the pond entirely and wandered further south through the city. It was his hope that a brief walk would calm the growing empty feeling that upset his belly. It was a futile exercise he knew, but he couldn't bear to stand still any more. He was not at all accustomed to waiting games. What little patience he knew was already spent and a knot of frustration had been left in its place.<br>
<br>
He moved briskly through the tunnel that bridged Felwithe proper with its south end only to find the object of his frustrations standing just beyond its egress. The sight of her brought him to an immediate stop. He absently muttered her name, &quot;Candra.&quot;<br>
<br>
Willius peered at the human enchantress before him, looking her up and down. Her long, dark hair was brushed smooth and fell down her back in an elegant line. She wore a black gown that teetered on the razor's edge between style and scandal and contrasted sharply with her creamy complexion. But all this was merely a frame for the twin masterpieces that were her eyes. It seemed to Willius that they caught the wan light and reflected it back a hundred fold; sparkling, mesmerizing violet.<br>
<br>
Willius knew he could lose himself in those eyes. What he didn't realize was that he already had.<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/belvenelite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=candraverbena>Candra Verbena</A> at: 5/21/03 7:21:13 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#AB8C5B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/belvenelite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=candraverbena>Candra Verbena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Regular</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(5/21/03 7:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=99.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~eden444/images/candra_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possession</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The City of High Elves - Felwithe<br>
<br>
South Felwithe</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Candra took in the mountain of a man standing before her with an easy smile. His heart was beating faster than it should, making him ruddy and flushed. Beads of sweat wet the red moustache and the muttonchops that added to his barbarian flair and rough edges. She idly wondered if his excited state was the product of the liquor that she smelled on his breath, the thickening heat of the summer night, or the enchantment of adoring grace that always surrounded her. She made a guess that it was a combination of the three.<br>
<br>
Willius seemed satisfyingly surprised by her approach, although shock soon gave way to a wave of hungered emotions Candra took in with the pleasure of a gourmet sampling a new dish. &quot;Willius,&quot; she spoke his name the way he liked to hear it; soft and slow.<br>
<br>
The barbarian shaman responded with a hungry and boring grin of lust. His thoughts, in all likelihood never strayed beyond his most base desires. His only reaction was to shift his stance to shrug off his obvious discomfort. &quot;Good ta see ye again, lass. It's been some time.&quot;<br>
<br>
Candra's cherry lips parted in a smile meant to thrill. &quot;It's been only a day since we last spoke, Willius.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;A very long day,&quot; Willius replied. He peered about curiously then looked at Candra with a question &quot;And who is yer escort tonight? I doubt ya came alone.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Doubt? No, but you certainly hope</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. The enchantress kept that thought to herself, but did not try to conceal the mischief that brought it to mind. &quot;I arrived on Jeez's arm, but it seems Fayeth has stolen him away from my side to discuss matters of faith and devotion. Having no genuine interest in either quality and feeling the onset of a mild headache I excused myself to take a quiet stroll away from the solstice celebration.&quot;<br>
<br>
