<br>
&quot;Ya let me,&quot; Willius countered.<br>
<br>
&quot;No, I didn't. It wasn't like that.&quot; An obvious lie, but she remained unwilling to live with knowledge of that truth.<br>
<br>
&quot;And ya liked it, I think.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Arrogant bastard!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Candra was losing ground with this argument and she knew it. She'd lost the upper hand and with that control of the situation. She needed time to think and that was the one thing Willius was not willing to give her. With a sigh she turned about and cast her gaze towards the heavens to take in the velvety night sky, the diamonds that twinkled against it and the silver sorcery of the full moon.<br>
<br>
